<p align="center"><h2><span id="title">Clean Landscape of small Pixels</span></h2><img id="icon" src="../icons/img_CleanRas.png" /></p>

<p><span id="section">Brief Description</span></p>

<p>Returns a raster with all pixels smaller than the structure removed. User can determine how many iterations should be performed.</p>

<p><span id="section">Parameters</span></p>
<ul>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input image list (-il): </span>Image list to perform computation on.</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
	<span>[param] Output Image (-out): </span>Output image.</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
	<span>[param] Available RAM (-ram): </span>Available RAM</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
	<span>[param] Expression (-exp): </span>The mathematical expression to apply. Use im1b1 for the first band, im1b2 for the second one...</p>
	</li>
</ul>

<p>
<span id="section">Limitations</span>
</p>

<p>None</p>
